# Tool Call Formatting

Tool use is formatted using XML-style tags. The tool name is enclosed in opening and closing tags, and each parameter is similarly enclosed within its own set of tags. Here's the structure:

<tool_name>
<parameter1_name>value1</parameter1_name>
<parameter2_name>value2</parameter2_name>
...
</tool_name>

For example:

<read_file>
<path>src/main.js</path>
</read_file>

Always adhere to this format for the tool use to ensure proper parsing and execution.

# Tools

{% for tool in tools %}
## {{ tool.name }}

Description: {{ tool.description }}

Parameters:
{% for param_name, param_schema in tool.parameters.items() %}
- {{ param_name }}: {% if param_schema.required %}(required){% endif %} {{ param_schema.description }}
{% endfor %}

{% for example_name, example_tool_call in tool.examples.items() %}
Example #1: {{ example_name }}
<{{ example_tool_call.name }}>
{% for param_name, param_value in example_tool_call.parameters.items() %}
<{{ param_name }}>{{ param_value }}</{{ param_name }}>
{% endfor %}
</{{ example_tool_call.name }}>
{% endfor %}
{% endfor %}
